  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're creating a countdown for a surprise party. Before the guest arrives, everyone has to stay quiet. You want your program to print the same \"Shhh...\" message a few times to build suspense before yelling \"Surprise!\"\r\n\r\n1. Define a function called `stay_quiet()` that prints\r\n\r\n   ```\r\n   🤫 Shhh... they're coming!\r\n   ```\r\n\r\n2. Call the function **three times** to build suspense.\r\n\r\n3. Then, add one more line of code outside the function to print\r\n\r\n   ```\r\n   🎉 SURPRISE!\r\n   ```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nUse functions to control repetition, and use `print()` on its own when you only need to say something once.\r\n\r\nUse the **UMPIRE** strategy to understand what's happening, make a plan, test your output, and explain your thinking.",
